22/09/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The Athens 2004 Organising Committee announced on Friday (19 September) that it plans to give 6,000 unemployed people temporary jobs related to preparations for next year's Olympic Games. 
Those eligible for the programme should be between 18 and 40 years of age and currently registered as unemployed, according to Labour Minister Dimitris Reppas. 
The jobs would last from three to 11 months. 
The EU is co-financing the programme.
In other news Friday, Prime Minister Costas Simitis said reducing unemployment, increasing real incomes and developing all regions of the country would be the priorities of the next government. 
His ruling PASOK party faces a tough battle in spring elections for another term. 
(ANA - 19/09/03)
